Relevant mandatory provisions of the Slovenian law:
Requirements stated below are based on the assumption that the borrower / consumer is resident in Slovenia at the time of Extension of Credit:

5.1: A loan agreement shall be concluded in Slovenian language (Consumer Protection Act);

5.2: PF shall provide a consumer with the information needed to compare different offers in order to take an informed decision on whether or not to conclude a credit agreement (pre-contractual information) (Consumer Credit Act);

5.3: Credit agreements shall be drawn up on paper or on another durable medium (Consumer Credit Act);

5.4: A loan agreement shall contain all required information as prescribed under the Consumer Credit Act (Consumer Credit Act);

5.5: Granting credits on basis of obtained Permit (Consumer Credit Act);

5.6: Costs of a warning letter shall not exceed real costs of the cost of producing and sending such letter (Consumer Protection Act);

5.7: Interest for late payment shall not exceed the amount as prescribed in the Code of Obligations (Consumer Protection Act, Code of Obligations, Statutory Default Interest Rate Act);

5.8: Loan agreement cannot stipulate annual percentage rate (“APR”) exceeding 200 % of the APR that is twice a year published by Bank of Slovenia (Consumer Credit Act).

Non-compliance with requirements listed in point 5) above shall be sanctioned as follows:

Breach under 5.1: A fine in the range from EUR 3,000 to 40,000 may be imposed on the PF; a borrower has a right to challenge a loan agreement;

Breach under 5.2: A fine in the range from EUR 12,500 to 125,000 may be imposed on the PF; establishment of nullity of the loan agreement may be requested;

Breach under 5.3: A fine in the range from EUR 12,500 to 125,000 may be imposed on the PF; a borrower has a right to rescind an agreement within one month of the date of the first payment under the agreement;

Breach under 5.4: A fine in the range from EUR 12,500 to 125,000 may be imposed on the PF; a borrower has a right to rescind an agreement within one month of the date of of the first payment under the agreement;

Breach under 5.5: A fine in the range from EUR 12,500 to 125,000 may be imposed on the PF; a loan agreement is considered null;

Breach under 5.6: A fine amounting to EUR 1,200 may be imposed on the PF; no consequences on the loan agreement;

Breach under 5.7: A fine from EUR 1,200 may be imposed on the PF; contractually agreed penalty interest exceeding penalty interest as prescribed in the Code of Obligations is considered null;

Breach under 5.8: A fine in the range of EUR 12,500 to 125,000 may be imposed on the PF; contractually agreed APR exceeding 200 % of the APR that is twice a year published by Bank of Slovenia is considered null.

