Offences under the Consumer Credit Law (106(I)/2010) may be dealt with by the following actions:
(a)	a warning is issued to cease the act(s) which is/are causing the breach;
(b)	corrective measures are implemented to rectify the breach;
(c)	an administrative fine is imposed up to 5% of the annual business revenue of the offender which shall not exceed €500,000;
(d)	in case the offence is continuing an administrative fine of up to €1,700 may be imposed for each day that the offence is  continuing; or
(e)	a court order may be issued against any person which is responsible for the offence in order to restrict the offence.

Offences under the Remote Provision of Credit to Consumers law (242(I)/2004) may be dealt with by the following actions:
(a)	a warning is issued to cease the act(s) which is/are causing the breach;
(b)	an administrative fine is imposed up to 5% of the annual business revenue of the offender which shall not exceed €171,000;
(c)	in case the offence is continuing an administrative fine of between €85.50  to €342 may be imposed for each day that the offence is  continuing; or
(d)	a court order may be issued against any person which is responsible for the offence in order to restrict the offence.
